Remove stalk and core from the @red pepper{1} and @yellow pepper{½} and cut into thin slices. Peel and finely dice the @garlic clove{1}. Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{2} leaves. Cut the @cocktail tomato{1} in half and then into quarters. Chop the @British chicken thighs{2} into bite-sized chunks. Boil @water{600%ml} with the @chicken stock pot{1}.

Set hob to high heat and heat @oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{}. Season the chicken well with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the chicken to the pan and fry for a few minutes. Once it is brown on all sides, remove and keep to the side.

Add another @olive oil{1%tbsp} into the frying pan. Add the peppers and tomatoes. Cook for a few mins until they've softened up. Add in the garlic, @rosemary{2} and the @diced chorizo{⅓}.

After ~{3%minutes}, add half the parsley and the @basmati rice{1}. Cook for a few minutes until the rice absorbs the oil.

Add the chicken stock and chicken. Give everything a good stir. Reduce heat to medium-low and cook for ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Don't stir - a good paella always has a crusty bottom!

Once the liquid has soaked up, take the paella off the heat. Cover with a clean #tea towel{} and leave for ~{5%minutes}. Serve with the remaining parsley and big wedges of @lemon{½}.

> This chicken Paella has managed to sneak in some spicy chorizo for double meaty goodness. It's a real crowd-pleaser that you will love to cook again and again.